<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-03-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="544" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d544">
                        <head>544. Telegram 1652 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d544fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                                611.93/3–2056. Confidential; Limit Distribution.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-03-20">March 20, 1956, 5
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d544-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d544-1"/>
                        <p>1652. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>. Re Deptel
                            1769.</p>
                        <p>Reports conversations New Delhi not (repeat not) yet received other than
                            summaries of memos contained Deptel 1750. Tokyo conversation also not
                            received.</p>
                        <p>Draft history talks transmitted by letter March 17.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1"><hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>